  "name": "Peanut Allergy - Epinephrine Auto-Injector Prescription",
  "description": "Tests ability to find peanut allergy patients via epinephrine auto-injector prescriptions. Synthea encodes the auto-injector as RxNorm 1660014 (1 ML epinephrine 1 MG/ML Injection). Note: epinephrine has many indications beyond peanut allergy (other anaphylaxis triggers, cardiac arrest, etc.) — making this a high-cross-indication test.",
  "prompt": "Find patients prescribed epinephrine for severe allergic reaction risk.",
  "prompts": {
    "naive": "Find patients on epinephrine.",
    "broad": "Find patients prescribed an epinephrine auto-injector — typically prescribed for severe allergic reactions including anaphylaxis from food allergens such as peanuts.",
    "expert": "Search MedicationRequest with RxNorm code 1660014 (1 ML epinephrine 1 MG/ML Injection). Query: MedicationRequest?code=http://www.nlm.nih.gov/research/umls/rxnorm|1660014"
  },
